{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DZPmL3tsoFtzWs4FRYuAiC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# How to Set Up Claude Code\n     2â†’\n     3â†’This guide covers configuring Cloche containers to use\n     4â†’[Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code) as the coding agent.\n     5â†’\n     6â†’## Prerequisites\n     7â†’\n     8â†’- A working Cloche installation ([Installation guide](INSTALL.md))\n     9â†’- Claude Code installed on the host (`npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`)\n    10â†’- An active Claude Code session on the host (run `claude` once to authenticate)\n    11â†’\n    12â†’## How Authentication Works\n    13â†’\n    14â†’Cloche automatically copies your host's `~/.claude/` directory and `~/.claude.json`\n    15â†’file into each container at `/home/agent/.claude` and `/home/agent/.claude.json`. This\n    16â†’reuses your existing Claude Code session so containers authenticate without needing an\n    17â†’API key.\n    18â†’\n    19â†’The files are copied (not bind-mounted) so each container gets its own copy, avoiding\n    20â†’concurrent write conflicts when multiple runs execute in parallel.\n    21â†’\n    22â†’## Dockerfile\n    23â†’\n    24â†’Your `.cloche/Dockerfile` must install Claude Code via npm:\n    25â†’\n    26â†’```dockerfile\n    27â†’FROM cloche-base:latest\n    28â†’USER root\n    29â†’\n    30â†’# Install Node.js (required for Claude Code)\n    31â†’RUN apt-get update \\\n    32â†’    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n    33â†’    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    34â†’\n    35â†’# Install Claude Code\n    36â†’RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    37â†’\n    38â†’# Add your project's build dependencies here\n    39â†’# RUN apt-get install -y ...\n    40â†’\n    41â†’USER agent\n    42â†’```\n    43â†’\n    44â†’## Workflow Configuration\n    45â†’\n    46â†’Claude is the default agent, so no explicit configuration is needed. These are\n    47â†’equivalent:\n    48â†’\n    49â†’```\n    50â†’// Implicit â€” claude is the default\n    51â†’step implement {\n    52â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    53â†’  results = [success, fail]\n    54â†’}\n    55â†’\n    56â†’// Explicit\n    57â†’step implement {\n    58â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    59â†’  agent_command = \"claude\"\n    60â†’  results = [success, fail]\n    61â†’}\n    62â†’```\n    63â†’\n    64â†’Default arguments passed to Claude Code:\n    65â†’\n    66â†’```\n    67â†’-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\n    68â†’```\n    69â†’\n    70â†’Override with `agent_args` if needed:\n    71â†’\n    72â†’```\n    73â†’step implement {\n    74â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    75â†’  agent_args = \"-p --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n    76â†’  results = [success, fail]\n    77â†’}\n    78â†’```\n    79â†’\n    80â†’## Using an API Key Instead\n    81â†’\n    82â†’If you prefer to use an API key rather than session reuse, set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in\n    83â†’the daemon's environment. Cloche passes it into containers automatically:\n    84â†’\n    85â†’```bash\n    86â†’export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"sk-ant-...\"\n    87â†’cloched &\n    88â†’```\n    89â†’\n    90â†’This works alongside session reuse â€” Claude Code will use the API key if no session\n    91â†’is available.\n    92â†’\n    93â†’## Verifying the Setup\n    94â†’\n    95â†’Run a quick test workflow:\n    96â†’\n    97â†’```bash\n    98â†’cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Print hello world\"\n    99â†’```\n   100â†’\n   101â†’Check logs to confirm Claude Code is executing:\n   102â†’\n   103â†’```bash\n   104â†’cloche logs <run-id>\n   105â†’```\n   106â†’\n   107â†’## Troubleshooting\n   108â†’\n   109â†’**Claude Code not found in container**: Make sure your Dockerfile installs\n   110â†’`@anthropic-ai/claude-code` via npm and that Node.js is available.\n   111â†’\n   112â†’**Authentication errors**: Run `claude` on the host to ensure your session is active.\n   113â†’Cloche copies `~/.claude/` at container creation time, so a stale or missing session\n   114â†’on the host means containers won't authenticate.\n   115â†’\n   116â†’**Permission errors on `~/.claude`**: Cloche runs `chown -R agent:agent` on the copied\n   117â†’auth files at container startup. If you see permission errors, check that your\n   118â†’Dockerfile does not override the entrypoint.\n   119â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ea6a4db-317b-4116-946b-dfa5f420f957","uuid":"e668d8d5-da9e-4e5e-b9bb-ce7c7748c448","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/agent-setup-claude.md","content":"# How to Set Up Claude Code\n\nThis guide covers configuring Cloche containers to use\n[Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code) as the coding agent.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- A working Cloche installation ([Installation guide](INSTALL.md))\n- Claude Code installed on the host (`npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`)\n- An active Claude Code session on the host (run `claude` once to authenticate)\n\n## How Authentication Works\n\nCloche automatically copies your host's `~/.claude/` directory and `~/.claude.json`\nfile into each container at `/home/agent/.claude` and `/home/agent/.claude.json`. This\nreuses your existing Claude Code session so containers authenticate without needing an\nAPI key.\n\nThe files are copied (not bind-mounted) so each container gets its own copy, avoiding\nconcurrent write conflicts when multiple runs execute in parallel.\n\n## Dockerfile\n\nYour `.cloche/Dockerfile` must install Claude Code via npm:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\n\n# Install Node.js (required for Claude Code)\nRUN apt-get update \\\n    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install Claude Code\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n\n# Add your project's build dependencies here\n# RUN apt-get install -y ...\n\nUSER agent\n```\n\n## Workflow Configuration\n\nClaude is the default agent, so no explicit configuration is needed. These are\nequivalent:\n\n```\n// Implicit â€” claude is the default\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n\n// Explicit\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  agent_command = \"claude\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\nDefault arguments passed to Claude Code:\n\n```\n-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\n```\n\nOverride with `agent_args` if needed:\n\n```\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  agent_args = \"-p --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n## Using an API Key Instead\n\nIf you prefer to use an API key rather than session reuse, set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in\nthe daemon's environment. Cloche passes it into containers automatically:\n\n```bash\nexport ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"sk-ant-...\"\ncloched &\n```\n\nThis works alongside session reuse â€” Claude Code will use the API key if no session\nis available.\n\n## Verifying the Setup\n\nRun a quick test workflow:\n\n```bash\ncloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Print hello world\"\n```\n\nCheck logs to confirm Claude Code is executing:\n\n```bash\ncloche logs <run-id>\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n**Claude Code not found in container**: Make sure your Dockerfile installs\n`@anthropic-ai/claude-code` via npm and that Node.js is available.\n\n**Authentication errors**: Run `claude` on the host to ensure your session is active.\nCloche copies `~/.claude/` at container creation time, so a stale or missing session\non the host means containers won't authenticate.\n\n**Permission errors on `~/.claude`**: Cloche runs `chown -R agent:agent` on the copied\nauth files at container startup. If you see permission errors, check that your\nDockerfile does not override the entrypoint.\n","numLines":119,"startLine":1,"totalLines":119}}}
