{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01La8tU8y69jot7m4xgSRnTT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Cloche Usage\n     2â†’\n     3â†’Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4â†’workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5â†’container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6â†’results to a git branch.\n     7â†’\n     8â†’## Core Concepts\n     9â†’\n    10â†’- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11â†’- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12â†’- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13â†’- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14â†’- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15â†’\n    16â†’## Workflow DSL\n    17â†’\n    18â†’Workflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19â†’declared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20â†’no orphans, entry point exists).\n    21â†’\n    22â†’### Minimal Example\n    23â†’\n    24â†’```\n    25â†’workflow \"develop\" {\n    26â†’  step implement {\n    27â†’    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    29â†’  }\n    30â†’\n    31â†’  step test {\n    32â†’    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33â†’    results = [success, fail]\n    34â†’  }\n    35â†’\n    36â†’  implement:success -> test\n    37â†’  implement:fail -> abort\n    38â†’  test:success -> done\n    39â†’  test:fail -> abort\n    40â†’}\n    41â†’```\n    42â†’\n    43â†’### Step Configuration\n    44â†’\n    45â†’| Key | Type | Description |\n    46â†’|-----|------|-------------|\n    47â†’| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48â†’| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49â†’| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50â†’| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51â†’| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52â†’| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53â†’| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54â†’| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55â†’| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56â†’| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57â†’\n    58â†’A step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59â†’\n    60â†’### The `file()` Function\n    61â†’\n    62â†’`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63â†’(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64â†’templates:\n    65â†’\n    66â†’```\n    67â†’prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68â†’```\n    69â†’\n    70â†’### The `container {}` Block\n    71â†’\n    72â†’Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73â†’\n    74â†’**Step level** â€” per-step container config:\n    75â†’```\n    76â†’step code {\n    77â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78â†’  container {\n    79â†’    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80â†’    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81â†’    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82â†’  }\n    83â†’  results = [success, fail]\n    84â†’}\n    85â†’```\n    86â†’\n    87â†’**Workflow level** â€” defaults for all steps:\n    88â†’```\n    89â†’workflow \"develop\" {\n    90â†’  container {\n    91â†’    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92â†’    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93â†’    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94â†’  }\n    95â†’  ...\n    96â†’}\n    97â†’```\n    98â†’\n    99â†’Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TQUiMsxdg5gnwAGacmevRe","session_id":"8ea6a4db-317b-4116-946b-dfa5f420f957","uuid":"b1f682d9-f30f-450f-a4f3-5dd279c417f1"}
