{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fydt7mAs1xbG9EymQhjnHR","type":"tool_result","content":"   100â†’\n   101â†’### The `host {}` Block\n   102â†’\n   103â†’Can appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104â†’with a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105â†’\n   106â†’```\n   107â†’workflow \"main\" {\n   108â†’  host {\n   109â†’    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110â†’  }\n   111â†’  ...\n   112â†’}\n   113â†’```\n   114â†’\n   115â†’Supported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116â†’`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117â†’\n   118â†’### Wiring Syntax\n   119â†’\n   120â†’Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121â†’\n   122â†’```\n   123â†’implement:success -> test\n   124â†’implement:fail -> abort\n   125â†’test:success -> done\n   126â†’test:fail -> fix\n   127â†’```\n   128â†’\n   129â†’### Wire Output Mappings\n   130â†’\n   131â†’Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132â†’\n   133â†’```\n   134â†’step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135â†’```\n   136â†’\n   137â†’Path expressions:\n   138â†’\n   139â†’| Expression | Meaning |\n   140â†’|---|---|\n   141â†’| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142â†’| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143â†’| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144â†’| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145â†’| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146â†’\n   147â†’If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148â†’text, only bare `output` works.\n   149â†’\n   150â†’### Retry Loops\n   151â†’\n   152â†’Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153â†’\n   154â†’```\n   155â†’test:fail -> fix\n   156â†’fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157â†’fix:fail -> abort\n   158â†’```\n   159â†’\n   160â†’Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161â†’\n   162â†’```\n   163â†’step fix {\n   164â†’  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165â†’  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166â†’  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167â†’}\n   168â†’```\n   169â†’\n   170â†’### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171â†’\n   172â†’Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173â†’\n   174â†’```\n   175â†’test:success -> lint\n   176â†’test:success -> quality\n   177â†’```\n   178â†’\n   179â†’### Collect (Join)\n   180â†’\n   181â†’Synchronize parallel branches:\n   182â†’\n   183â†’```\n   184â†’collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185â†’collect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186â†’```\n   187â†’\n   188â†’`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189â†’\n   190â†’### Comments\n   191â†’\n   192â†’Line comments with `//`:\n   193â†’\n   194â†’```\n   195â†’// This is a comment\n   196â†’implement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197â†’```\n   198â†’\n   199â†’## Result Protocol\n   200â†’\n   201â†’Steps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202â†’\n   203â†’```\n   204â†’CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205â†’```\n   206â†’\n   207â†’For example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208â†’\n   209â†’Rules:\n   210â†’- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211â†’- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212â†’- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213â†’- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214â†’- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215â†’\n   216â†’## Prompt Assembly\n   217â†’\n   218â†’When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219â†’\n   220â†’1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221â†’2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222â†’3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223â†’4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224â†’\n   225â†’The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226â†’\n   227â†’## Agent Command Resolution\n   228â†’\n   229â†’Priority (highest to lowest):\n   230â†’1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231â†’2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n   232â†’3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233â†’4. Default: `claude`\n   234â†’\n   235â†’### Fallback Chains\n   236â†’\n   237â†’Comma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238â†’\n   239â†’```\n   240â†’agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241â†’```\n   242â†’\n   243â†’- **Command not found / failed to start** â€” try next command\n   244â†’- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** â€” try next command\n   245â†’- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** â€” use that result (no fallback)\n   246â†’- **Exit 0** â€” use result (no fallback)\n   247â†’- **All commands fail to start** â€” step returns an error\n   248â†’- **Last command crashes without marker** â€” step returns `fail`\n   249â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TQUiMsxdg5gnwAGacmevRe","session_id":"8ea6a4db-317b-4116-946b-dfa5f420f957","uuid":"fcd08725-f01a-46d3-8444-d545707b94e4"}
